# Android & Capacitor build rules

When the user asks to build the Android app, fix a blink/crash, or run Gradle, follow these rules.

## 1. Cleartext and Pixel compatibility (blink / WebView)

- **Always** keep `android:usesCleartextTraffic="true"` on the `<application>` element in [`erp-mobile-app/android/app/src/main/AndroidManifest.xml`](erp-mobile-app/android/app/src/main/AndroidManifest.xml).
- **Always** keep [`erp-mobile-app/android/app/src/main/res/xml/network_security_config.xml`](erp-mobile-app/android/app/src/main/res/xml/network_security_config.xml) wired via `android:networkSecurityConfig` so local and HTTP traffic work during development.
- In [`erp-mobile-app/capacitor.config.ts`](erp-mobile-app/capacitor.config.ts), keep `android.allowMixedContent: true` for Android.

After changing `capacitor.config.ts`, run Capacitor sync so the config is copied into Android assets (e.g. `npm run cap:sync:android:prod` or `npx cap sync android`).

## 2. PowerShell commands only (Windows)

- Do **not** suggest Unix-only commands such as `rm -rf`.
- To remove directories, use: `Remove-Item -Path "path" -Recurse -Force` (quote paths that contain spaces).

## 3. Correct Gradle directory

- Do **not** run `gradlew` from the repo root or from `erp-mobile-app` alone.
- **Always** `cd` (or `Set-Location`) to `erp-mobile-app\android` before `.\gradlew.bat clean`, `.\gradlew.bat assembleDebug`, etc.
- Use Windows-style invocation: `.\gradlew.bat` (not `./gradlew`).

## 4. Sync before native build

- From **`erp-mobile-app`**, run **`npm run cap:sync:android:prod`** before building the debug/release APK so `dist` and Capacitor config are up to date in the Android project.
- For a non-production web bundle, `npm run cap:sync:android` is the alternative; default to prod when the user is testing production-like APKs.

